f_rho = function(rho){
  N=10000
  K=matrix(c(1,rho,rho,1),2,2)
  A=chol(K)
  xx=matrix(, nrow = N, ncol = 2)
  for (i in 1:N){
    K
    K3=rnorm(2)
    xx[i,]=t(A)%*%K3
  }
  plot(xx,main=cat("Rho ",rho))
  return(xx)
}
for (i in seq(-0.9,0.9,0.1)){
xx=f_rho(i)
}

Exercice 3

library(rgl)#Pour la visualisation 3d
N=10000
K1=matrix(c(14,8,3,8,6,-3,3,-3,26),3,3)
m=c(-1,0,2)
f2_rho = function(K,m,N){
  A=chol(K)
  x=matrix(, nrow = N, ncol = 3)
  #X1=rnorm(N,mean = m[1])
  #X2=rnorm(N,mean = m[2])
  #X3=rnorm(N,mean = m[3])
  for (i in 1:N){
    Z3=rnorm(3)+m
    Z3
    x[i,]=t(A)%*%Z3
  }
  plot3d(x,col = 'red')
  return(x)
}
x=f2_rho(K1,m,100000)
moy=apply(x,2,mean)
moy
## [1] -3.749384 -2.142111  5.454529
